<section class="sec" id="comparison">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">01</span>
      <span class="sec-name">Side by side</span>
      <span class="sec-aside">every Talkiatry fact sourced from talkiatry.com</span>
    </div>

    <h2>The full comparison, <span class="em">with sources</span></h2>
    <p class="answer-lede">
      Talkiatry only sees patients whose insurance they accept &mdash; their FAQ says no self-pay. ADHD Advisor never involves insurance: <strong>$199 flat, known before you book,</strong> with a clinician who focuses on ADHD.
    </p>
    <p class="sec-intro" style="margin-top:-28px;">Where Talkiatry is stronger, the table says so &mdash; in their own words, from their own site.</p>

    <p class="swipe-hint">Swipe to compare &#8594;</p>
    <div class="comp-wrap">
      <table class="comp-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th class="col-label"></th>
            <th class="col-adhd">
              <span class="col-name">ADHD Advisor</span>
              <span class="col-sub"><span class="stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span> 4.7/5 on Trustpilot</span>
            </th>
            <th class="col-talk">
              <span class="col-name">Talkiatry</span>
              <span class="col-sub">facts from talkiatry.com, June 2026</span>
            </th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">Built for</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              <span class="win-tag">The core difference</span>
              <span class="cell-lead">ADHD &mdash; 100% of the practice.</span>
              <span class="cell-note">Adult ADHD evaluation, medication management, therapy &amp; coaching</span>
            </td>
            <td class="cell-talk">
              General psychiatry across 11+ conditions
              <span class="cell-note">ADHD, anxiety, depression, bipolar disorder, OCD, insomnia and more</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">Without insurance</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              <span class="win-tag">The only option of the two</span>
              <span class="cell-lead">$199 total, flat &mdash; price known before you book.</span>
              <span class="cell-note">HSA/FSA accepted</span>
            </td>
            <td class="cell-talk">
              <span class="cell-na">Not available. &#8220;We do not currently offer a self-pay option&#8221; &mdash; talkiatry.com FAQ</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">With in&#8209;network insurance</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              Flat fee either way; superbill provided for possible out-of-network reimbursement
              <span class="cell-note">Reimbursement depends on your plan and isn&#8217;t guaranteed</span>
            </td>
            <td class="cell-talk">
              <span class="cell-lead">In-network with major insurers.</span>
              <span class="cell-note">&#8220;Most Talkiatry patients pay around $30 out of pocket per visit&#8221; &mdash; talkiatry.com</span>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">First appointment</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              <span class="cell-lead">45-minute live video evaluation with a doctor or NP.</span>
              <span class="cell-note">Your clinician reviews your intake before the call</span>
            </td>
            <td class="cell-talk">
              Video visit with a psychiatrist or psychiatric NP
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">How fast</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              <span class="cell-lead">Often same-day or next-day.</span>
            </td>
            <td class="cell-talk">
              &#8220;Appointments in days&#8221; &mdash; talkiatry.com
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="row-label">Medication</td>
            <td class="cell-adhd">
              <span class="cell-lead">Stimulant and non-stimulant options, depending on your state.</span>
              <span class="cell-note">Prescribed by your clinician if they determine it&#8217;s appropriate after your evaluation</span>
            </td>
